ActHealth of Animals Act
PrecisRegulations Amending the HEALTH OF ANIMALS REGULATIONS by establishing a definition for specified risk material (SRM), by requiring removal of SRM from cattle aged 30 months or older and by prohibiting the export and use of SRM in any form as food for humans.
